<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
An IBM expansion card added to a computer system, enabling a color monitor to display 16 colors at a screen <a title="Resolution" href="Resolution">resolution</a> of up to 640 x 350 pixels at 21.8 kilohertz (KHz). It was an improvement over <a title="CGA" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/CGA">CGA</a>, but still was only capable of displaying text with an 8 x 14-dot character cell. It was superseded by <a title="VGA" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/VGA">VGA</a>. 
</p>
